Tamweel Second-Quarter Profit Surges on Fewer Provisions

-- B y   A r i f   S h a r i f
-- 
2011-07-19T14:39:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-19/tamweel-second-quarter-profit-surges-on-fewer-provisions-1-.html
Tamweel PJSC (TAMWEEL) , the mortgage company
majority controlled by  Dubai Islamic Bank PJSC (DIB) , said second-
quarter profit jumped fivefold as bad-loan provisions dropped.  Net income advanced to 27.7 million dirhams ($7.5 million)
from 5.4 million dirhams a year earlier, according to a
statement on the Dubai bourse website today. Impairment
provisions fell 66 percent to 13.5 million dirhams and operating
income dropped 9.4 percent to 148.8 million dirhams.  Dubai Islamic Bank paid 374.7 million dirhams, or 1 dirham
a share, in cash and stock in September to raise its ownership
in Tamweel to 58.3 percent from 21 percent. The move was part of
a plan to boost mortgage financing in Dubai.  Tamweelâ€™s shares rose 0.9 percent to 87.6 fils on the  Dubai
Financial Market  at the 2:00 p.m. close today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
